# Event Pipeline

## Flow

```
query.submitted → ingestion.completed → embedding.completed → knowledge.mined
  → research.task.dispatched (×N) → research.task.completed (×N)
  → synthesis.completed
```

Step Functions handles research fan-out in prod. Local: simplified sequential fan-out.

## Event naming

`eventforge.<domain>.<action>` — e.g. `eventforge.query.submitted`

## Required fields (every event)

`event_id`, `correlation_id`, `job_id`, `timestamp`, `schema_version`, `payload`

Define JSON Schema in `shared/events/` first. Mirror as Pydantic in `backend/src/eventforge/events/schemas/`.

## Stage map

| Event in | Worker | Event out | Stores |
|----------|--------|-----------|--------|
| query.submitted | Ingestion | ingestion.completed | sources → Postgres |
| ingestion.completed | Embedding | embedding.completed | vectors → Postgres (pgvector) |
| embedding.completed | Knowledge | knowledge.mined | entities → Postgres |
| research.task.dispatched | Research | research.task.completed | notes → Postgres |
| all research done | Synthesis | synthesis.completed | report → Postgres |

## Resilience

- SQS `maxReceiveCount: 3` → `eventforge-dlq`
- Idempotency: `processed_events(event_id PK, worker_name, processed_at)`
- Terminal failure: emit `pipeline.failed`, update JobStage → `failed`, push to SSE
- LLM calls: 3 retries, exponential backoff

## Queues (LocalStack + prod)

`eventforge-ingestion`, `eventforge-embedding`, `eventforge-knowledge-mining`, `eventforge-research`, `eventforge-synthesis`, `eventforge-dlq`
